Quadrotor UTFSM

Linus Casassa <lcasassa@gmail.com>
Electronic engineering student UTFSM

Based on Olimex STM32-H103 Header Board.

1x Header Board for STM32 Cortex-M3                               - $ 40.95 US - http://www.sparkfun.com/products/8559
1x IMU Digital Combo Board - 6 Degrees of Freedom ITG3200/ADXL345 - $ 64.95 US - http://www.sparkfun.com/products/10121
2x XBee Pro 50mW Wire Antenna - Series 2 (ZigBee Mesh)            - $ 40.95 US - http://www.sparkfun.com/products/10421
1x RX 8 channels walkera
1x TX 6 channels walkera
4x ESC with simon's firmware                                      - https://github.com/sim-/tgy
4x Brushless motors                                               - AXI 2808/24
2x APC 10x4.7 Slow Flyer Propeller                                - $ 2.99 US - http://www.amainhobbies.com/ APC10047
2x APC 10 x 4.7 Slow Flyer Pusher Propeller                       - $ 4.19 US - http://www.amainhobbies.com/ APC10047SFP

Do not forget the cables to connect everything.

Thanks to the libopencm3 proyect for ther library!



This is the control diagram for each axis:

   / \    -------  / \    -------    --------      -------
---| |----| PID |--| |----| PID |----| Quad |------| 1/s |--------
   \ /    -------  \ /    -------    --------   |  -------   |
    |               |                           |            |
    |               -----------Gyro--------------            |
    |                                                        |
    ---------------------------Angle--------------------------

With the gyro, the accelerometer and a kalman filter you can get the Angle.
The input is the Angle reference given by the joystick.

